  "prompt": "Is there a way to for my Google Calendar to manage my Office 365 Exchange Cal that doesn't involve using the Subscribe Option?",
  "response": "Yes, there are a few ways to sync your Office 365 Exchange Calendar with Google Calendar:\n\n1. Direct Google Sync Method:\n- Go to Google Calendar settings\n- Add your Office 365/Exchange email address\n- Choose \"Add Calendar\" and select \"From email address\"\n- This creates a direct two-way sync\n\n2. Microsoft Graph API:\n- Developers can use this for more advanced synchronization\n- Requires some technical setup\n\n3. Third-Party Sync Tools:\n- Apps like SyncGene, Sync2, or CloudWork\n- Often offer more robust two-way syncing\n- Some have free and paid versions\n\n4. Google Workspace (Formerly G Suite) Integration:\n- If you have a Google Workspace account, it offers more direct Exchange integration\n- Provides more seamless calendar synchronization\n\n5. Outlook Desktop App Method:\n- In Outlook, you can add your Google account\n- This can create a sync between the two calendars\n\nEach method has pros and cons regarding complexity, cost, and sync accuracy. The best approach depends on your specific needs and technical comfort level.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these methods?",
